net.smartcosmos.catalogs.model.context

Interface IPageEntry

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IAccountContext, IAccountDomainResource<IPageEntry>, IDomainResource<IPageEntry>, IMoniker, INamedObject<IPageEntry>, ITypedObject, IUrnNamespace
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    PageEntry

    public interface IPageEntry
extends IAccountDomainResource<IPageEntry>, INamedObject<IPageEntry>, ITypedObject
    Use an IRelationship to create a link between a Page Entry and a specific object. For example, if someone scanned an RFID tag related to a Model ABC123 of an HVAC, then the page entry could link to that IObject entry to easily access all the metadata and multimedia files associated with that object.

    In essence, the IPageEntry is really just a pointer to a set of metadata; there is no text, no content per se on the IPageEntry itself!
